ent characterized by strong, often dictatorial control of political and economic affairs, and often by warlike nationalism and brutal suppression of political dissidents and ethnic minorities.&quot;<br><br>And most of the modern fascists have been far LEFT wingers. The Hitler, Stalinist, Franco, Castro, etc. Sorry bub..you are incorrect. Look at the governments of those nations. The emphais was on a strong centralized government and economy, All were based on left-wing ideals.<br><br>Many would call many mulsim &quot;theocracies&quot; fascist. I would agree with that. <br><br>If you take theocracies (governments controlled by religion) out of the picture, there is no such thing as a right-wing fascist government. Right-wing=less centralized control. it would lend itself more toward anarchy rather than fascism. This is of course if true right-wing ideals are followed and maintained.<br><br>And for me personally...I would rather have to take care of myself than have to rely on the government to support me entirely. I guess it is just my personality. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwallaceoffv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WallaceofFV</A> at: 10/25/01 5:17:21 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufaldoran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faldoran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/25/01 5:37:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Left Wingers</span><hr size=1> Dictionary definitions 101:<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> fascism</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> any ideology or movement inspired by Italian Fascism, such as German National Socialism; any <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> right-wing</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> nationalist ideology or movement with an authoritarian and hierarchical structure that is fundamentally opposed to democracy and liberalism. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> any ideology, movement, programme, tendency, etc., that may be characterised as <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> right-wing</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, chauvinist, authoritarian, etc.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Fascism</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (note capital F): the political movement, doctrine, system, ore regime of Benito Mussolini in Italy. Fascism encouraged militarism and nationalism, organising the country along hierarchical authoritarian lines.<br><br>Fascism is right-wing, not left. It doesn't matter how many 'examples' you give as being left-wing.<br><br>I won't add any more to this, as your last post has been editted twice while I was typing this. Anything that I put now might have no relation to what your post will be when I hit the Post button. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwallaceoffv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WallaceofFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/25/01 5:59:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Left Wingers</span><hr size=1> I read the exact definiton you just posted. It did not include right wing. Can you post the link to that please? Any half-wit political scientist will be able to tell you that the European Fascists were left wingers. They centralized governmental and economic control. That is the DEFINITION of left wing. The Italian Fascists were the most LEFT WING OF ALL. By far. Now, if that was the definition presented, they need to learn what right-wing means. It means decentralization. LESS control of the government and less authoritarianism. The European fascists were often characterized as totalitarianists, which is generally an exclusively left-wing term.<br><br>German National Socialism---SOCIALISM is a move to the left no matter which way you slice it. Either you made up the definition or the author of that dictionary definition has some homework to do. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwallaceoffv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WallaceofFV</A> at: 10/25/01 6:01:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufaldoran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faldoran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 94<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/25/01 7:08:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Left Wingers</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>I read the exact definiton you just posted. It did not include right wing. Can you post the link to that please?<br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Hmm, did you not see the word 'right' next to the word 'wing'? I cannot post a link, as the internet will not link directly to my bookshelf. The definitions came from the Collins English Dictionary.<br><br>A quick scout for my DVD version of the Encyclopedia Brittanica (I haven't the shelf space for the book format), gives an Oxford University Press definition of the following:<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> fascism</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> noun[i/] (mass noun) an authoritarian and nationalistic <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> right-wing</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> system of government and social organization. (in general use) extreme <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> right-wing</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, authoritarian, or intolerant of views or practice.<br><br>No doubt if you access the online (subscription only) service of the Oxford University Press dictionary, you will see a similar definition.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>Either you made up the definition or the author of that dictionary definition has some homework to do.<br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Is that your answer? The definition does not agree with your personal definition, and so you accuse the poster of 'making it up'? Why does that not surprise me. But no, I did not 'make it up'. I will therefore forward your view that the definitions are wrong to the relevant University presses and producers of these reference books. I find it scandalous that respected educational sources should mislead in such a way, by giving such spurious definitions.<br><br>This post is in reply to edited version of your previous post, which was last edited at &quot;10/25/01 6:01:58 </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufaldoran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faldoran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9